								<div class="title" id="post-title-771247">
																		Okay, then...
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/misterflames" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(438028); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=438028&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252530" alt="MisterFlames" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=438028)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/misterflames" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(438028); return false;" >MisterFlames</a></span> <span class="odate time_1272665339 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Apr 2010 22:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-771247">
									

<p>For those of you who are interested in what <a href="/scp-130">the Post Office</a> delivers, I've started a little list. I plan on building on it, of course, but treat this as an Experiment Log, should you come up with an interesting idea for a parcel. I ask that people hold to the following rules.</p>
<ul>
<li>Please do not mail SCPs through the Post Office: I have tried to avoid the idea of the Post Office generating SCPs, although I do reserve the right to change my mind.</li>
<li>Run ideas past the writers of particular Avatars: I did ask Clef and Rights, and I'll probably ask others, too. It's just common courtesy.</li>
</ul>
<p>The missives can be from the past and the future (or possible futures), and I believe they should hold personal touches for people. It's a game of psychology, what would be an interesting thing to happen to a person, either wonderful or hideous?</p>
<p>Just remember that the Foundation isn't going to deliver it, unless it's absolutely vital.</p>
<p>Have fun!</p>

							</div>

								
					
